At least 16 firearms, including a revolver, rifle and pistols were recovered by police during the weekend s crime prevention operations. Busted were 18 suspects in Gauteng s Moffatview, Sandton, Atteridgeville, Midrand, Eden Park, Jeppe, Johannesburg Central and Orange Farm. The suspects will be charged with the possession of unlicensed firearms during their appearances in various courts today. In one of the incidents in Sandton, a woman owner of a restaurant and an employee were offloading goods from a vehicle. They were attacked by two men, one armed with a knife and the other with a firearm. ALSO READ: Gauteng government reaches out to LGBTI community Spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Lungelo Dlamini said the woman was stabbed and the employee shot in the upper body. He died at the scene. The suspects fled without taking anything. One suspect who had a firearm was pointed out by members of the community and arrested not far from the scene of crime, Dlamini said. A firearm was recovered. He will be charged with attempted murder, murder and possession of an unlicensed firearm. The woman who was stabbed was treated at a local hospital and discharged. During stop and search operations in Moffatview, Jeppe and Nelmapius, police searched suspicious people and vehicles. Police are also appealing to the public to report any suspicious vehicles and people. Information may be forwarded to Crime Stop at 08600-10111 or the nearest police station at all hours. Information that may lead to the arrests of suspects involved in serious and violent crimes may be rewarded. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.